  "body": "We may be able to use a checkpoint state directly in processing `AggregateAndProof`s, rather than dialing the state forward to the `attestation.data.slot`.\r\nDialing the state forward is a small bit of work (hashing as a result of `processSlot`) that may be avoided.\r\nInvestigate using the checkpoint state directly.\r\nSee https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/master/packages/lodestar/src/chain/validation/aggregateAndProof.ts#L84\r\n\r\nWould save 21% of CPU time\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2021-03-24 20-51-47](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/112374951-fbcdd400-8ce2-11eb-8436-a220d74ce19a.png)\r\n",
